=== Available Platform Roles ===

{{PRODUCT}} defines a set of global roles as well as a set of predefined roles that allow for fine-granular sharing of resources. The available roles are summarized in the following.

{| class="sortable flTable2" style="width:800px;"
|-
!style="background-color: #E9E9E9"| Role
!style="background-color: #E9E9E9" |Description
|-
|style="background-color: white"| admin:
|style="background-color: white"| Platform admin with full permissions
|-
|style="background-color: #EEEEEE; border-right: 0"| user:
|style="background-color: #EEEEEE"| Role for general user permissions
|-
|style="background-color: white"| guest:
|style="background-color: white"| Platform guest with limited functionality
|-
|style="background-color: #EEEEEE; border-right: 0"| file-admin:
|style="background-color: #EEEEEE"| Access to download files (including user uploads, all streaming downloads, as well as backup and config files)
|-
|style="background-color: white"| file-user:
|style="background-color: white"| Access to download files (including user uploads and public streaming downloads)
|-
|style="background-color: #EEEEEE; border-right: 0"| permission-admin:
|style="background-color: #EEEEEE"| Permission admin with full rights for permission management
|-
|style="background-color: white"| permission-domainadmin:
|style="background-color: white"| Permission domain admin with domain-restricted rights for permission management
|-
|style="background-color: #EEEEEE; border-right: 0"| permission-assigner:
|style="background-color: #EEEEEE"| Permission assigner has access to the share resource UI
|-
|style="background-color: white"| sparql-query:
|style="background-color: white"| Role permitting the execution of SPARQL SELECT and CONSTRUCT queries
|-
|style="background-color: #EEEEEE; border-right: 0"| sparql-update:
|style="background-color: #EEEEEE"| Role permitting the execution of SPARQL UPDATE queries
|-
|style="background-color: white"| wiki-admin:
|style="background-color: white"| Wiki admin granting write access to resources as well as revision management
|-
|style="background-color: #EEEEEE; border-right: 0"| wiki-editor:
|style="background-color: #EEEEEE"| Wiki editor granting limited write access (e.g. no widgets) to resources
|-
|style="background-color: white"| wiki-view:
|style="background-color: white"| Wiki view granting read access to general resources
|-
|style="background-color: #EEEEEE; border-right: 0"| platform-base:
|style="background-color: #EEEEEE"| Base role for platform functionality that can be used for role composition
|-
|style="background-color: white"| platform-views:
|style="background-color: white"| Role for giving access to standard platform views (i.e., table, graph and pivot)
|}